<subSubSection id="1A585A6E0AA207D6F6F8A2E41B0AF5F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="E697F8D86B0DD9F7A82533CB7A5C2860" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F58DFB6C1CEDFE962047180551D1318" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="78B82399B1C8B21702169A97A1814251" authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Stenochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenochironomus okialbus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okialbus">
<emphasis id="7EDBF15A22C5ED4298DB8D79F8512866" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Stenochironomus okialbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other related species by a combination of characters: wing with dark markings in the middle and apex; superior volsella short and small, spatulate, with four or five long setae; inferior volsella elongate, with 2-4 long setae and a slender terminal spine; posterior margin of tergite IX with 8-10 setae and eight spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF8DB0A0E754651BCCFCCDB397FAAA08" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="9B7990D1BC19EBBB0A118EAB2D20E3C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC6CBD9ACB2262CD9A3F9D41816BAEBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Male imago (N = 3). Total length 2.94-3.98, 3.62 mm. Wing length 1.80-1.85 mm. Total length / wing length 1.85-2.20, Wing length / length of pro-femur 178-1.88.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55A542D8DC422F83FEA67EB4B2688114" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="8B2089FBB7EA4436170FFB6E1A607AF7" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Coloration</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="165CD7B51C93E2406376DB9E7EA2F756" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Male adult (holotype) of Stenochironomus baishanzuensis Song &amp; Qi, sp. nov. A hypopygium in dorsal view B hypopygium in ventral view C superior volsella." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.81403.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694000" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">8</figureCitation>
). Body almost pale yellowish or white, except postnotum with spot area and tergite IV-VII brown; wing with dark pigmentation on median and apical parts; all legs pale yellow with dark knees and apex of tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C48F92A987C44BC7ACDFAFE77249B210" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="CDA2FC38DB7C1A557C152A019A7C2F54" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.10-1.25, 1.12, ultimate flagellomere 430-660, 580 
<normalizedToken id="1D96424839ABA77E5A3D739D9DF64E92" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Temporal with 12-16, 14 setae, including 7-8, 7 inner verticals, 4-7, 6 outer verticals and 1-2, 2 postorbitals. Clypeus with 12-20, 17 setae. Tentorium 155-220, 190 
<normalizedToken id="2BF13047B0AEA1E98423F92B03516E02" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, 30-53, 44 
<normalizedToken id="389DA3B259C8D76CD5AE4521E0659185" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide. Palpomere lengths (μm): 33-48, 37; 40-65, 55; 123-195, 170; 85-125, 116; 130-218, 194. Palpomere ratio (5th /3rd) 1.05-1.21, 1.13.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6ABBC955A6C4374CBD45752264F25986" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="CBB7CBC8070225711F3AFD940B5E4A89" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Thorax.</emphasis>
Dorsocentrals 14-21, 18; acrostichals 9-12, 11; prealars 5-6, 6; Scutellum with 7-12 setae in two rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B42F8973B6ED3046DFF8F34C0CB9B0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="2DCF51022C2F78B5BD141FA46069485F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="935BAA7FDAA1F883050227446B56F4D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
VR 1.06-1.10, 1.08. Brachiolum with 1-2, 2 setae. Distribution of setae on veins: R, 20-29, 25; R1, 21-39, 31; R4+5, 49-53, 51. Squama with 10-18, 14 setae. Anal lobe normally developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="78154354BD8733AAA4F4DF806C6FA0BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="79705B58F7C3D9FBB5B171A5ADF411CD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore leg: width at apex of tibia 53-63, 58 
<normalizedToken id="2309C5C2640B53A5392B7C708A91C4D6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, tibia with blunt scale 35-50, 44 
<normalizedToken id="10A2D25EF78AC071AB37DDB4AAF74565" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Mid leg: width at apex of tibia 53-70, 61 
<normalizedToken id="75D4141C3B424489FA9BA4EE05532AE2" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, tibia with two apical spurs 43-53, 48 and 45-58, 52 
<normalizedToken id="F1DCF1593417A8EED017B85EEF773278" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Hind leg: width at apex of tibia 58-73, 64 
<normalizedToken id="03EC6869E8D7C15EB22B29735C12EAF8" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, tibia with two apical spurs 45-55, 51 and 45-56, 52 
<normalizedToken id="355A6507EEA19A4E624A253846AF2AB4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Lengths (in 
<normalizedToken id="51D4AD7EE028FD3681FE47C5621869DE" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and proportions of legs as in Table 
<tableCitation id="A9081CFCB9B3CD75368CE3C239CDDEC0" captionStart="Table 6" captionStartId="T6" captionText="Table 6. Male adult of Stenochironomus okialbus. Lengths (in µm) and proportions of legs (N = 3, except where otherwise stated)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/F0C98DA29C88F35B18B3F2F5439AA385" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" tableUuid="F0C98DA29C88F35B18B3F2F5439AA385">6</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
